A GLASGOW family is trying to find a mystery bus driver who saved their dad's life.&nbsp;Shelley Montague posted an appeal on Facebook after her father collapsed while running for a bus in Sighthill.She said a bus driver started CPR until an ambulance arrived, possibly saving his life.She wrote: &quot;We're hoping the power of Facebook can help us find the person who saved our dad's life.&quot;On Saturday morning, 25th April, he was running for the 6:10am, number 57 bus at the Calder vaults, Sighthill across from the St Rollox Tesco.&quot;He collapsed and his heart stopped and we've been told the bus driver(s) started CPR and continued that until the ambulance came.&quot;She said they wanted to find those who were helping her dad to thank them.Her dad is recovering, she said.The appeal was shared more than 200 times, and has also spread to Twitter, with Scottish Conservative leader Ruth Davidson appealing for Twitter to 'do its thing' and help the Montague family identify the bus driver who helped their father.Do you know who the driver is? Contact the Evening Times on 0141 302 6580.